<issue_to_address>
**🚨 suggestion (security):** Token verification is skipped when header token is missing even if a verification token is configured.

Because verification only happens when `header.token` is present, a request with a missing token header is still accepted even when `creds.verificationToken` is configured. If `verificationToken` is meant to be a strict check, consider rejecting requests when it’s configured but `token` is absent or falsy, instead of treating them as valid.

```suggestion
    // Verify token if configured
    const token = body.header?.token;
    if (appId) {
      const key = `${platform}:${appId}`;
      const creds = this.credentialsByKey.get(key);

      if (creds?.verificationToken) {
        if (!token) {
          log('handleLarkWebhook: missing token for %s', key);
          return new Response('Missing verification token', { status: 401 });
        }

        if (creds.verificationToken !== token) {
          log('handleLarkWebhook: token mismatch for %s', key);
          return new Response('Invalid verification token', { status: 401 });
        }
      }
    }
```
